In [[telecommunication]], the term '''frequency assignment''' has the following meanings: 

<b>1.</b>  [[Authorization]], given by an Administration, for a [[radio station]] to use a [[radio frequency]] or radio frequency [[channel]] under specified conditions 

<b>2.</b>  The process of authorizing a specific frequency, group of frequencies, or frequency [[band]] to be used at a certain location under specified conditions, such as [[bandwidth]], [[power]], [[azimuth]], [[duty cycle]], or [[modulation]].  <i>Synonym</i> <b>radio frequency channel assignment.</b> <i>See</i> <b>[[administration]] (def. #1).</b>

Source: from [[Federal Standard 1037C]] and from [[MIL-STD-188]]

